Key Match Events: Sikandar Raza picked up three for 25 against Pakistan
Mohammed Nawaz caught for 22 from the penultimate ball of the match off Brad Evans
Shaun Masood steadied the ship with a composed 44 before being stumped off a Raza wide
Sean Williams (31) found the boundary three times
Shadab Khan (three for 23) bowled Sean Williams
Late runs from Evans (19 off 15 balls) gave Zimbabwe the lift they ultimately needed
Rilee Rossouw scored the first century of the tournament with 109 off 56 balls
Quinton de Kock shared a 168-run stand with Rilee Rossouw
Post-Match Reflections: Sikandar Raza said, 'I really, truly believe in this group of boys. Since I’ve been part of Zimbabwe cricket, I would rate that as the best victory we’ve had. There’s no better stage. This is the World Cup, the biggest stage of all.'
Babar Azam said, 'Today we were not up to the mark in all three departments'
Miscellaneous Highlights: Pakistan’s much-vaunted pace attack bowled too full in the powerplay, conceding 47 runs
Bangladesh succumbed to 101 in 16.3 overs in reply
Anrich Nortje collected four for 10 while left-arm wrist-spinner Tabraiz Shamsi finished with three for 20
Rohit Sharma, Virat Kohli and Suryakumar Yadav helped India make it two wins from two with an impressive 56-run victory over the Netherlands
